      <section eId="sec_190_05">
        <num>190.05</num>
        <heading>Issuing a bad check</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_190_05__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>As a drawer or representative drawer, he utters a check knowing\nthat he or his principal, as the case may be, does not then have\nsufficient funds with the drawee to cover it, and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_190_05__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>he intends or\nbelieves at the time of utterance that payment will be refused by the\ndrawee upon presentation, and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_190_05__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>payment is refused by the drawee upon\npresentation; or\n  2.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_190_05__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>He passes a check knowing that the drawer thereof does not then\nhave sufficient funds with the drawee to cover it, and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_190_05__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>he intends or\nbelieves at the time the check is passed that payment will be refused by\nthe drawee upon presentation, and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_190_05__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>payment is refused by the drawee\nupon presentation.\n  Issuing a bad check is a class B misdemeanor.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
